#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:361
msgid "It is recommended that a Command Station/Programmer provide full read and write access to the 8 Physical registers (``000``) to (``111``) for all values of 8-bit data. This allows a user to directly manipulate Physical registers 1 (``000``) to 8 (``111``) and CV data in any manner. The Command Station/Programmer documentation should indicate the numbering or naming scheme in use, and how these correspond to the 8 Physical Registers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:363
msgid "In Physical Register Addressing Mode two instruction types (``C``) are defined:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:371
