#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:486
msgid "Write register/CV contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:375
msgid "Verify Register Contents (``0``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:376
msgid "This instruction type causes a Verify operation that compares the eight (8) bit data value ``DDDDDDDD`` with the contents of the specified three (3) bit register address ``RRR``. If these two values are equal, the Digital Decoder shall generate an acknowledgment as defined in Section D."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:378
msgid "Write Register Contents (``1``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:379
#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:494
msgid "This instruction type causes a Write operation that stores the eight (8) bit data value ``DDDDDDDD`` into one of the eight registers as specified by the three (3) bit register address ``RRR``. Upon completion of all write operations, the Digital Decoder may respond with an acknowledgment as defined in Section D."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:384
msgid "Service Mode Instruction Packets for Paged CV Addressing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:386
msgid "Implementations that require access to a larger number of Configuration Variables than possible using just the 8 Physical Registers can use an extended 3-byte programming format called Paged CV Addressing. If a decoder does not implement Paged CV Addressing, it must not respond to Paged CV programming commands when the page register has a value greater than 1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:388
msgid "Paged CV Addressing implements access to all 1024 Configuration Variables through advanced usage of the 8 Physical ``registers`` or storage locations. The first four registers are used as Data Registers on a particular page. The sixth register holds the current page number. The following diagram shows the order of packet sequence for paged mode:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:394
msgid "5 or more Writes to the Page Register"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:396
msgid "one ore more times:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:401
msgid "5 or more Verifies to a single Data Register 1-4"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:404
msgid "5 or more Writes to a single Data Register 1-4"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:405
msgid "6 or more identical Write or Reset packets (Decoder Recovery Time from write to Data Register)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/S-9.2.3-service-mode-programming.rst:409
msgid "Within a verify or write sequence, the Command Station/Programming may cease sending packets and continue with the next step in the sequence when either a decoder acknowledgment is successfully received or the number of packets specified to be transmitted is completed."
msgstr ""

